  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dba\u0da7 \u0da9\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dbb\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd4\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d87\u0dbb\u0db9\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Focus on starting a dollar account for food security",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Dr. Suren Batagoda, Chairman of the Presidential Committee on Food Security, said that if Sri Lanka's food security is not established, the people of the country will have to face a major nutritional deficiency next year.",
        "Yesterday (29) afternoon, a discussion was held at the Ministry of Wildlife and Forest Resources under the chairmanship of Minister Mahinda Amaraweera about the work to be carried out by the Ministry of Agriculture on food security.",
        "Dr. Suren Batagoda, secretaries of the ministry Mr. Rohana Pushpakumara and Mr. Chandra Herath as well as Moneragala and Hambantota district secretaries and a group of officials participated in the discussion.",
        "It was emphasized here about the breakdowns that have occurred in our country's milk, egg and poultry products. At present, liquid milk production has decreased by 19.8 percent, chicken meat production by 12.1 percent and egg production by 34.9 percent.",
        "If this situation continues, there is a risk of complete collapse of poultry and egg production next year. It was emphasized here that the livestock industry has collapsed due to the lack of maize and other products required for the production of animal feed, as well as the shortage of chemical fertilizers and fuel.",
        "To avoid this situation, there is a need of 900 million dollars for the future activities of agriculture. Dr. Suren Batagoda, Chairman of the President's Committee on Food Security, proposed to focus on starting a dollar account for the future development of agriculture as there is difficulty in obtaining such amount from the government treasury at once.",
        "He emphasized that Sri Lankans working in foreign countries, international organizations and other aid groups can arrange to get the amount for this account.",
        "Accordingly, the Minister of Agriculture Mahinda Amaraweera instructed the Secretary of the Ministry to prepare a Cabinet Memorandum to maintain a dollar account.",
        "Apart from that, it was suggested to start a program of providing urea fertilizer for the maize grown in this year's season as well as providing seeds and urea fertilizer for growing maize in more land in the next season. Accordingly, the minister mentioned that 25,000 hectares of Moneragala, 5000 acres of Maduru Oya, 500 acres of Kantale and 3000 acres of Kandakadu farm are planned to be cultivated.",
        "Dr. Suren Batagoda also mentioned that in order to achieve the success achieved in the Sri Lankan agriculture in 2018, those reforms should be implemented again.",
        "Due to the reforms brought by Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera, who was the Minister of Agriculture at that time, it was possible to obtain the highest rice harvest and maize harvest in the last four decades in the 2018/19 season. It was also emphasized in this discussion that it was possible to achieve great improvement in other crop productions as well."
      ],
